    "Starting from the biological model of a neuron, in 1958, Rosenblatt modeled the first, simplest artificial neural network with a single neuron as a computational unit that (i) receives a certain number of inputs, (ii) carries out calculations, and (iii) returns the results of the calculations (Rosenblatt, 1958).",
